        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-05T21:37:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, good point.\n\nThe easiest (?) for Fuchsia would probably have been to port it to Go as that\u0027s what the Fuchsia team favours for \"script\"-type things. Considering Android though, perhaps a plain ol\u0027 C++ binary will be best.\n\nChromium does some forwarding back to a host process because there the test server is quite complex, but there\u0027s a lot of code to manipulate those connections, it\u0027s sometimes flaky, and it means that the device can\u0027t run tests standalone without being hooked to a parent which seems a bit awkward sometimes (in that the tests can\u0027t run fire-and-forget).",
      "parentUuid": "af0925e9_7f56dd22",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 400,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 403,
        "endChar": 11
      },
