    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "16657791_f6e66f97",
        "filename": "util/numeric/checked_address_range.cc",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 135,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-05T21:10:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In deciding what to do here:\n\n1. I know that Fuchsia only builds for 64-bit architectures now (namely x86-64 and arm64). Is that an ongoing guarantee, or is there a possibility that there may be a 32-bit architecture hosting Fuchsia in the future?\n\n2. Even if the answer to (1) is “32-bit is not foreclosed,” it seems that a multi-bitted Fuchsia, in which a single system might host both 64-bit and 32-bit user spaces, may never happen for other reasons. Reasonable assumption?\n\nOn the basis of the answers to these questions, we may be able to rule out cross-bitting on Fuchsia altogether. It’d be good to know this up front, since it may impact some of these existing interfaces.",
      "revId": "4337a2ee984aecf28ea5206083177a14d316d6a2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b7643fb9_31c9de85",
        "filename": "util/numeric/checked_address_range.cc",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 135,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-05T21:37:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e In deciding what to do here:\n\u003e \n\u003e 1. I know that Fuchsia only builds for 64-bit architectures now (namely x86-64 and arm64). Is that an ongoing guarantee, or is there a possibility that there may be a 32-bit architecture hosting Fuchsia in the future?\n\nYes, it\u0027s absolutely 64-bit only AFAIK. +cpu to confirm if there\u0027s an Official Statement of that somewhere.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e 2. Even if the answer to (1) is “32-bit is not foreclosed,” it seems that a multi-bitted Fuchsia, in which a single system might host both 64-bit and 32-bit user spaces, may never happen for other reasons. Reasonable assumption?\n\u003e \n\u003e On the basis of the answers to these questions, we may be able to rule out cross-bitting on Fuchsia altogether. It’d be good to know this up front, since it may impact some of these existing interfaces.\n\nFuchsia/Zircon seem pretty solidly 64-bit only, so I think in the platform-specific code we\u0027re safe to simplify by not considering cross-bitness. I think 128-bit pointers at some point in the future might be more likely than 32-bit. :)",
      "parentUuid": "16657791_f6e66f97",
      "revId": "4337a2ee984aecf28ea5206083177a14d316d6a2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
